# Files NEVER copied into the Docker build context.
#
# The Dockerfile already uses explicit COPY for each runtime file (no
# `COPY . .`), so most of these are belt-and-suspenders. But .dockerignore
# also keeps these out of the *build context* sent to the Docker daemon,
# which speeds up builds (less to hash) and prevents accidents if anyone
# ever adds a wildcard COPY later.

# Tier-3 integration validation suite — explicitly out-of-image by design.
# Hits the deployed compactor as a black box; lives in git for versioning
# but must never end up at /opt/* in the running container.
tests/

# Build / push / scout logs from local rebuilds.
*.log
build-*.log
push-*.log
scout-*.log

# Git, dev env, CI metadata.
.git/
.github/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.editorconfig

# Local env files — secrets live here.
.env
.env.local
.venv/
.test-venv/

# Throwaway verification scripts (compactor/_verify_*.py)
compactor/_verify_*.py

# Python caches.
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# IDE.
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp

# OS junk.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Docs that don't belong in the image.
README.md
ROADMAP.md
CHANGELOG.md
TESTING.md
RUNPOD_DEPLOY.md
compactor/V2_PLAN.md
